org.middleheaven.quantity.money
Class CentsMoney

java.lang.Object
  org.middleheaven.quantity.money.CentsMoney
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<org.middleheaven.quantity.money.Money>, AlgebricStructureElement<org.middleheaven.quantity.money.Money>, GroupAdditiveElement<org.middleheaven.quantity.money.Money>, Amount<org.middleheaven.quantity.money.Money,Currency>, Quantity<Currency>
public class CentsMoney
extends java.lang.Object

Represents an amount of money that only represents quantity to the currency maximum fraction digits. Example, for USD the minimum representation possible is 0.01 USD. Any operation that results in less that this value will result in an exception.

distribute

public CentsMoney[] distribute(int installments)
Allocate this money amount in n installments. All money is divided among the installments. If the devision remainder is not zero it is added to the first amount

Parameters:
percentages - an int arrays containing the percentages. Example int[]{30,30,40}
installments - the quantity of required installments
Returns:
an arrays of Money each of the same currency as this and containing the percentage of the amount

distribute

public CentsMoney[] distribute(int installments,

Parameters:
installments - the number of instalments to distribute into.
incrementedInstallment - The instalment to increment. 1 is the first, 2 is the second, etc...

allocate

public CentsMoney[] allocate(java.lang.Integer firstPercentage,
                             java.lang.Integer... percentages)
Allocate this money amount according to a percentage distribution All money is divided among the installments. If the devision remainder is not zero it is distributed among the first installments

Parameters:
percentages - an variable array of int, each representing a percentages. allocate(30,30,40). The sum must be 100
Returns:
an arrays of Money each of the same currency as this and containing the percentage of the amount
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if percentages is empty or it does not sum 100.

divide

public CentsMoney divide(int n)
Divides the amount equally between n installments So 100 divided by 3 will return 33,33 for a 2 fraction digits currency. The remainder is ignored.

Returns:
